Stage 1 - Virtual Environment Setup
-Installed VirtualBox on host system
-Created four virtual machines
 -Windows server 2022 (active directory domain controller)
 -Windows 10 (Domain-joined endpoint)
 -Kali Linux (Attack machine)
 -Splunk Server (Centralised logging and alerting) [sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y]
-Verified all systems boot successfully

Stage 2 - Splunk Install and Configure
-Created a custom NAT network 
 -All machines share the 192.168.10.0/24 subnet
-Statically assigned IP to splunk server and verified
-Updated packges and installed guest additions, utils
-Created shared folder 
 -Contains Splunk Enterprise
-Added user to vboxsf
-Created directory called 'share'
 -Mounted share folder to share directory (Active directory)
 -Installed Splunk Enterprise from share directory
-Confirgured to start Splunk on boot

